<br>
Take the Reaver/Valewalker style lines for example. Their styles include magical effects that proc. Making changes to DW/CD that, for example, allow Mercs to add a debuff proc to Dual-Shadows or a small PBAE spell to a Blademaster style would do wonders for these classes. Make the availabilty of these procs to only Mercs/BMs and make it level dependent. Also, let the Merc/Bm pick and choose the type of proc they want to add to their next style. <br>
<br>
I'm not saying make the classes become uber. Add timers for proc reuse to balance gameplay. Perhaps, make Flurry/TW/Dirt effects that proc off a style. Such changes would not only balance these classes, but also add significant depth.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=accualt>Accualt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#000000>(12/30/02 12:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=70.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Adding a proc line for BMs/Mercs</span><hr size=1> I don't want procs.<br>
